description:
Is there a hidden agenda behind the rapid push toward sustainable development? Could the events of the Middle Ages still be affecting us today? What information about church and state relationships is hiding in titles such as esquire and liege?
 What was the concession Britains King John made to Pope Innocent III? Is it binding today? 

Professor Walter J. Veith explores the issue of sustainable development and the fascinating history of Englands crown and its forfeiture to a religious power. What interests do world leaders such as Prince Charles, Al Gore, and the UN have in sustainable development? Whats behind the hype about sustainability, Mother Earth, and the green movement? 

How is it that Britains monarchs, who claim to be protectors of the Protestant church in England, where the insignia of Roman knights? What powers controls the secret societies and royal orders to which the British elite show their allegiance? Learn how it came about that England and its former colonies are all vassals which belong to Rome and how an agenda of worldwide control is being foisted on Earths inhabitants. History has startling answers to why we are seeing certain players on the world stage. Find out more in this significant and eye-opening presentation.
